SPRINGFIELD, Va. (AP) â€” A northern Virginia police officer fatally shot a presumably rabid coyote that had bitten several people after the animal also attacked him, authorities said Sunday. The Fairfax County officer was searching a wooded area for the coyote, which had bitten three people and two dogs in the vicinity a day earlier. The coyote bit the officer, who fired his gun to end the attack, the department tweeted. The animal was found dead nearby, and the officer was taken to a hospital for treatment. Lt. Dan Spital said the officer and community members who were bitten are expected to make a full recovery. Spital said authorities suspect the animal was rabid. Testing to confirm whether it had the disease will be conducted, he said.